messages.message:
Thanks for the context @Jessica / @jack.robbins

Do we have a pulse on how prominent this bug /error state appears for customers?

I don't _think_ we have anything that would directly track this event today, but if you have the URL where you saw that error, and the URL is unique, I can see if we have it in Google analytics. If not, we'd need to implement https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-2948, which we should start on later this month.
Yeah we can add an event for getting an access denied error for an app

@jack.robbins - the preferred route for design would be to have the App open in a new window once clicked

I'm curious to see what the traffic volume will show, but in the meantime this solution would provide a solution without exhaustive work. open to thoughts @Jessica
